over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcongress-stock-act-violations-senate-house-trading-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsider%20trading%20by%20members%20of%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20called%20James'%20inquiry%20a%20proper%2C%20even%20necessary%2C%20exercise%20of%20the%20power%20vested%20in%20an%20attorney%20general%20whose%20Manhattan%20office%20sits%20three%20blocks%20north%20of%20the%20Stock%20Exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20called%20her%20inquiry%20a%20politically%20motivated%20boondoggle%20that's%20doomed%20to%20fail.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20story%20of%20politics%2C%20not%20a%20story%20of%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richard%20Epstein%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20unanimity%20on%20two%20points.%20Proving%20insider%20trading%20is%20notoriously%20difficult.%20And%20whatever%20is%20happening%20behind%20the%20scenes%20is%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20nothing%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Manhattan%20attorney%20Armen%20Morian%2C%20a%20former%20financial%20crimes%20prosecutor%20for%20the%20New%20York%20AG's%20office%20who%20helped%20defend%20Trump%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-civil-fraud-verdict-whats-in-judge-engorons-decision-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJames'%20fraud%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292ededeb-3be2-493c-9320-d9a9cf405d7b%5C%22%3EAn%20800-pound%20gorilla%20of%20a%20statute%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inquiry%20is%20empowered%20by%20New%20York's%20Martin%20Act%2C%20a%20104-year-old%20statute%20that%20gives%20state%20attorneys%20general%20extraordinary%20powers%20to%20police%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20call%20the%20Martin%20Act%20the%20most%20powerful%20state%20securities-fraud%20law%20in%20the%20country.%20It%20allows%20the%20AG%20to%20issue%20subpoenas%2C%20grill%20suspects%20under%20oath%2C%20and%20file%20civil%20lawsuits%20or%20criminal%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202018%20essay%2C%20Epstein%20called%20the%20Martin%20Act%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchicagounbound.uchicago.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D13802%26context%3Djournal_articles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20800-pound%20gorilla%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20he%20said%20he%20still%20stands%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20prosecutes%20securities%20and%20real%20estate%20frauds%20and%20is%20used%20only%20rarely%20for%20insider%20trading%2C%20which%20is%20the%20illegal%20profiting%20off%20of%20stock%20tips%20not%20available%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20and%20three%20veterans%20of%20the%20AG's%20office%20who%20have%20brought%20prosecutions%20under%20the%20Martin%20Act%20say%20they've%20never%20heard%20of%20it%20being%20used%20to%20investigate%20insider%20tips%20involving%20government%20policy%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20Trump's%20on-and-off%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20novelty%20of%20James'%20inquiry%20does%20not%2C%20in%20itself%2C%20doom%20her%20effort%2C%20said%20a%20former%20financial%20crimes%20prosecutor%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%2C%20citing%20work%20constraints%20against%20speaking%20to%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20body%20of%20Martin%20Act%20insider%20trading%20law%20%E2%80%94%20just%20not%20on%20these%20exact%20facts%20%E2%80%94%20that%20has%20been%20developed%20over%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20prosecutor%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20remember%2C%20the%20facts%20of%20every%20case%20are%20always%20novel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250a146f9-ccaa-4a87-82bd-8069d03c9813%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20an%20AG%20inquiry%2C%20and%20how%20does%20it%20work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%26quot%3Binquiry%26quot%3B%20is%20what%20the%20New%20York%20AG's%20office%20calls%20the%20earliest%20stage%20of%20a%20probe%20%E2%80%94%20before%20subpoenas%20go%20out%2C%20explained%20former%20Executive%20Attorney%20General%20Manisha%20M.%20Sheth.%20Now%20a%20partner%20at%20Quinn%20Emanuel%20Urquhart%20%26amp%3B%20Sullivan%2C%20Sheth%20oversaw%20the%20AG's%20Division%20of%20Economic%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecurities%20inquiries%20can%20be%20sparked%20by%20whistleblower%20tips%20or%20by%20allegations%20that%20surface%20publicly%20in%20the%20press%20or%20a%20lawsuit%2C%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20handled%20by%20the%20state%20investor%20protection%20bureau%2C%20one%20of%20the%20six%20divisions%20Sheth%20once%20supervised%2C%20she%20said.%20There%2C%20prosecutors%20working%20with%20the%20AGs'%20research%20analysts%20and%20data%20scientists%20would%20begin%20by%20reviewing%20raw%20trading%20data%2C%20she%20said.%20They'll%20look%20for%20suspicious%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWere%20there%20spikes%20in%20trading%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20on%20April%209%2C%20in%20the%20hours%20before%20Trump%20posted%20on%20Truth%20Social%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-be-cool-buy-stocks-truth-social-tariffs-global-markets-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETHIS%20IS%20A%20GREAT%20TIME%20TO%20BUY%3C%2Fa%3E!!!%26quot%3B%20triggering%20a%20market%20upswing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20the%20bureau%20would%20send%20out%20a%20flutter%20of%20%26quot%3Binquiry%20letters%2C%26quot%3B%20authorized%20by%20the%20bureau's%20chief%20or%20deputy%20chief%20and%20signed%20by%20the%20assistant%20attorney%20general%20handling%20the%20matter%2C%20Sheth%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20letters%20can%20ask%20for%20documents%2C%20data%2C%20or%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20the%20recipient%20of%20an%20inquiry%20letter%20may%20volunteer%20to%20meet%20with%20the%20office%20to%20provide%20the%20requested%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooperating%20at%20this%20early%20stage%20is%20completely%20voluntary.%20If%20a%20case%20advances%20to%20the%20point%20that%20subpoenas%20are%20issued%2C%20an%20inquiry%20will%20have%20graduated%20to%20an%20investigation%2C%20Sheth%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20start%20with%20using%20trading%20data%20to%20show%20that%20no%20reasonable%20person%20would%20have%20engaged%20in%20these%20trades%20without%20that%20non-public%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anthony%20Capozzolo%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20and%20state%20prosecutor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20want%20to%2C%20at%20the%20least%2C%20build%20an%20initial%20case%20that%20shows%20it's%20very%20likely%20that%20the%20only%20motivating%20factor%20for%20these%20trades%20was%20this%20allegedly%20inside%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225311%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%20sits%20beside%20his%20lawyers%20at%20his%20civil%20fraud%20trial.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653490ac96908fd7cdb4b771%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222987%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrump%20sits%20beside%20his%20lawyers%20at%20the%202023%20civil%20fraud%20trial%20brought%20by%20James's%20office.%3Cp%3EShannon%20Stapleton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2229f492fd-cfb6-4da2-ba78-75ac340e0631%5C%22%3EMore%20roadblocks%2C%20these%20days%2C%20for%20gathering%20trading%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompiling%20trading%20data%20will%20be%20tougher%20these%20days%2C%20predicted%20Capozzolo%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Lewis%20Baach%20Kaufmann%20Middlemiss%20in%20Manhattan%20and%20a%20former%20federal%20and%20state-level%20prosecutor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPre-Trump%2C%20the%20AG%20would%20routinely%20and%20easily%20ask%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20for%20trading%20data%20that's%20not%20already%20publicly%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20the%20SEC%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20and%20he%20could%20potentially%20instruct%20the%20SEC%20not%20to%20cooperate%2C%26quot%3B%20leading%20to%20a%20subpoena%20battle%2C%20Capozzolo%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdentifying%20suspicious-seeming%20trading%20patterns%20is%20only%20the%20beginning%2C%20legal%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%2C%20solely%20as%20a%20hypothetical%2C%20that%20a%20Trump%20insider%20reaped%20a%20small%20fortune%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-share-price-trump-tariffs-valuation-sell-off-china-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20the%20dip%20in%20Apple%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20right%20before%20Trump%20announced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-nvidia-magnificent-7-tech-rally-trump-tariffs-trade-war-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariff%20carve-out%20for%20electronics%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20China%20that%20sent%20the%20stock%20soaring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20enough%20to%20prove%20insider%20trading%2C%20legal%20experts%20said.%20For%20that%2C%20James%20would%20need%20witnesses%20willing%20to%20testify%20that%20specific%20investments%20were%20prompted%20by%20improper%20insider%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20try%20to%20force%20people%20to%20tell%20them%20who%20was%20present%20in%20rooms%2C%26quot%3B%20Capozzolo%20said%20of%20prosecutors.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20difficulty%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20things%20may%20have%20happened%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20very%20upper-level%20Trump%20and%20MAGA%20acolytes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20anyone%20in%20Trump's%20circle%20would%20certainly%20fight%20an%20inquiry%20letter%20or%20subpoena%20%E2%80%94%20and%20do%20so%20loudly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou'll%20see%20an%20immediate%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Morian%2C%20who%20helped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccounting-fraud-trial-starts-former-aig-chairman-hank-greenberg-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprosecute%20AIG%20CEO%20Hank%20Greenberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20longest%20Martin%20Act%20case%20in%20the%20AG's%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt'll%20be%20lock%20and%20load.%20The%20minute%20any%20subpoena%20goes%20out%2C%20I%20would%20immediately%20intervene%20if%20I%20were%20in%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%20and%20say%20'Nope.%20Can't%20do%20it.%20Sorry.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuing%2C%20charging%2C%20or%20subpoenaing%20Trump%20is%20a%20non-starter%2C%20given%20executive%20privilege%20and%20presidential%20immunity%2C%20which%20bars%20prosecution%20for%20official%20acts%2C%20Morian%20said.%20(He%20predicts%20presidential%20immunity%20would%20extend%20to%20civil%20cases%20as%20well%20someday%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20that%20ever%20gets%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20AG%20subpoenas%20issued%20to%20members%20of%20the%20executive%20branch%20%E2%80%94%20cabinet%20members%20and%20the%20like%20%E2%80%94%20could%20also%20be%20challenged%20on%20executive%20privilege%20grounds.%20And%20investigating%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreedom-caucus-stock-trading-ban-congress-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estock%20trades%20of%20members%20of%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20result%20in%20challenges%20as%20well%2C%20Morian%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20overreach%20too%20far%2C%20you%20could%20easily%20see%20a%20private%20litigant%20taking%20this%20up%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20limiting%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20state%20attorneys%20general%20in%20ways%20we've%20never%20seen%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20is%20being%20probed%20by%20the%20DOJ%20for%20alleged%20mortgage%20fraud%2C%20an%20allegation%20she%20has%20called%20baseless%20and%20which%20her%20attorney%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frachel-cohen-big-law-abbe-lowell-trump-skadden-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbbe%20Lowell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20called%20%26quot%3Bimproper%20political%20retribution%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnewyork%2Fnews%2Fletitia-james-mortgage-fraud-allegations-attorney-response%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20CBS%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20her%20insider-trading%20inquiry%20advance%2C%20James%2C%20a%20Democrat%20who%20campaigned%20for%20AG%20on%20a%20promise%20of%20investigating%20Trump%2C%20would%20herself%20would%20face%20accusations%20of%20political%20retribution%20and%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Trump%20has%20decried%20James'%20investigations%20into%20his%20finances%20and%20business%20as%20baseless%2C%20%26quot%3Bracist%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fny-ag-letitia-james-donald-trump-dodging-her-subpoenas-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolitical%20witch%20hunt%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20A%20Trump%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20James'%20tariff-trade%20inquiry%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20the%20inherent%20difficulty%20of%20%3Cem%3Eproving%3C%2Fem%3E%20insider%20trading%20%E2%80%94%20of%20teasing%20out%20any%20illegality%20from%20the%20chaos%20of%20sudden%2C%20trillion-dollar%20market%20swings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20market%20turmoil%20whenever%20there's%20a%20major%20tariff%20initiative%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Epstein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20can%20anyone%20call%20it%20insider%20trading%20if%20thousands%20of%20investors%20are%20making%20similar%20trades%20for%20benign%20reasons%2C%20based%20on%20hunches%2C%20past%20experience%2C%20or%20dumb%20luck%2C%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20markets%20are%20this%20volatile%2C%20people%20make%20and%20lose%20money%20second%20to%20second%2C%20for%20any%20number%20of%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20agreed%20Morian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20contingent%20varia