3ENeurodivergent%20workers%20represent%20%26quot%3BAmerica's%20largest%20untapped%20talent%20pool%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20think%20tank%20said.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENeurodivergent%20workers%20could%20offer%20an%20important%20source%20of%20talent%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-looking-to-hire-laid-off-federal-workers-2025-4%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployers%20looking%20to%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20researcher%20estimates%20that%20as%20many%20as%201%20in%205%20people%20are%20neurodivergent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20startup%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20Israeli%20military%2C%20seeks%20those%20with%20varied%20thinking%20styles%20to%20train%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20his%20old%20desk%2C%20Alan%20Price%20sometimes%20found%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-feel-uncertain-worried-despite-trump-tariff-pause-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20to%20concentrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20he%20saw%20coworkers%20nearby%20or%20heard%20their%20footsteps%20as%20they%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20employee%20has%20a%20spot%20near%20a%20corner%20with%20a%20window%20on%20one%20side.%20The%20relative%20solitude%20helps%20him%20focus%2C%20Price%20said.%20When%20he%20needs%20a%20screen%20break%2C%20he%20takes%20in%20the%2011th-floor%20view%20overlooking%20downtown%20Boston.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20get%20easily%20distracted%2C%20so%20sitting%20near%20the%20window%20helps%20me%20because%20there%20is%20less%20foot%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%2C%2033%2C%20who%20identifies%20as%20neurodivergent%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20part%20of%20a%20group%20of%20more%20than%20250%20workers%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20often%20process%20information%20differently%2C%20as%20Price%20does.%20The%20team%20handles%20a%20range%20of%20back-office%20duties%20for%20the%20bank%2C%20including%20keying%20in%20hand-written%20credit%20card%20applications%20and%20preparing%20mailers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20like%20Price%20represent%20an%20often-overlooked%20segment%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20that%20could%20offer%20an%20important%20source%20of%20talent%2C%20especially%20for%20employers%20trying%20to%20staff%20hard-to-fill%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-taking-blue-collar-jobs-white-collar-hiring-slowdown-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemand%20for%20desk%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20fields%20like%20tech%20is%20slowing%2C%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-masculine-many-manufacturing-jobs-factories-trade-war-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployers%2C%20like%20manufacturers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20healthcare%20providers%2C%20still%20need%20people%20for%20a%20range%20of%20roles.%20Advocates%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buildwithtact.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0catering%20to%20neurodivergent%20job%20seekers%2C%20who%20can%20include%20those%20with%20autism%20spectrum%20disorder%2C%20dyslexia%2C%20or%20ADHD%2C%20could%20help%20meet%20some%20of%20that%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20big%20companies%2C%20including%20BofA%2C%20Dell%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20SAP%2C%20have%20programs%20designed%20to%20attract%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eneurodivergent%20workers%2C%20a%20group%20the%20think%20tank%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FEmbracing-Neurodiversity-at-Work-Unleashing-Americas-Largest-Untapped-Talent-Pool.pdf%3Fx85095%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabeled%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BAmerica's%20largest%20untapped%20talent%20pool.%26quot%3B%20Yet%2C%20many%20employers%20don't%20make%20overtures%20to%20this%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alan%20Price%20sits%20at%20a%20table%20with%20colleagues%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681230eba466d2b74ab4903b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlan%20Price%2C%20left%2C%20who%20identifies%20as%20neurodivergent%2C%20said%20he%20has%20found%20success%20at%20Bank%20of%20America%20in%20part%20because%20he%20continues%20to%20learn.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Bank%20of%20America%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad72727f-8c77-4ffd-a668-06fae34f6f6a%5C%22%3E1%20in%205%20people%20could%20be%20neurodivergent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAssessments%20vary%2C%20though%20one%20UK%20researcher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC7732033%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2015%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20people%20are%20%26quot%3Bneurominorities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20employers%2C%20the%20recruiting%20opportunity%20appears%20enormous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo-thirds%20of%20the%20neurodiverse%20population%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneurodiversity-employment.center.uconn.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighly%3C%2Fa%3E%20skilled%20yet%20unemployed%20or%20underemployed%2C%20according%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Connecticut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeloitte%2C%20the%20auditing%20and%20consulting%20giant%2C%20estimates%20that%20in%20the%20US%2C%2085%25%20of%20those%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20are%20unemployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20modest%2C%20yet%20growing%2C%20slice%20of%20employers%20is%20taking%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20job%20postings%20in%20the%20US%20that%20mention%20neurodiversity%2C%20excluding%20care-related%20roles%2C%20tripled%20from%200.1%25%20at%20the%20start%20of%202018%20to%200.3%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hiringlab.org%2F2025%2F03%2F18%2Fneurodiversity-inclusive-postings-are-rising%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efindings%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20March%20by%20Indeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226201edae-217d-4f55-b6ff-c96af656dd59%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInspired%20by%20the%20military%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20employer%20tapping%20into%20neurodivergent%20talent%20is%20Enabled%20Intelligence%2C%20a%20startup%20near%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20It%20reviews%20satellite%20images%20for%20the%20US%20military%20to%20identify%20and%20label%20objects%20like%20fighter%20jets.%20The%20data%20is%20then%20used%20to%20train%20AI%20models%20for%20security%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Kant%2C%20the%20company's%20CEO%20and%20founder%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20about%20half%20of%20Enabled%20Intelligence's%20workers%20describe%20themselves%20as%20neurodivergent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20starting%20the%20company%20in%202020%2C%20he'd%20heard%20from%20government%20officials%20about%20a%20need%20for%20high-quality%20data%20labeling.%20Inspired%20by%20a%20unit%20of%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20that%20includes%20servicemembers%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%2C%20Kant%20set%20out%20to%20recruit%20the%20workers%20necessary%20to%20take%20on%20detailed%20and%20routinized%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20thought%20that%20appealing%20to%20neurodivergent%20workers%20might%20be%20a%20way%20to%20achieve%20higher%20quality%20rates%20for%20data%20labeling%20than%20the%20industry%20standard%20of%2070%25.%20Kant%20remembers%20thinking%20he%20was%20onto%20something%20when%20he%20met%20with%20a%20government%20client%20who%20asked%20Kant%20who%20was%20doing%20his%20firm's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20like%2C%20'Are%20you%20sure%20you%20don't%20have%20subject%20matter%20experts%20in%20geospatial%20imagery%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKant%20explained%20that%20a%20specialist%20had%20trained%20the%20Enabled%20Intelligence%20workers%2C%20but%20that%20his%20team%20had%20only%20been%20working%20for%20three%20months.%20Then%2C%20the%20client%20dropped%20the%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20said%2C%20'Well%2C%20you're%20at%2097%25%20accuracy%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kant%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKant%20said%20the%20cognitive%20diversity%20within%20the%20company's%20teams%20results%20in%20more%20robust%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20only%20have%20one%20type%20of%20human%20brain%20or%20thought%20process%20labeling%20the%20data%2C%20then%20you're%20only%20going%20to%20have%20one%20approach%20for%20that%20AI%2C%20and%20you%20have%20an%20AI%20that%20doesn't%20work%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Kant%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b5ba9e7-c0be-4908-8258-674494578e8d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENavigating%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBringing%20more%20neurodivergent%20workers%20into%20the%20fold%20could%20require%20that%20some%20employers%20think%20differently%20about%20their%20workplaces.%20People%20identifying%20as%20neurodivergent%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FADHD%2Fcomments%2F1jrg6c1%2Fhow_do_people_feel_about_open_plan_offices_i_hate%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%3C%2Fa%3E%20stories%20online%20about%20the%20challenges%20of%20cacophonous%20open-plan%20offices%20or%20hot-desking%2C%20where%20employees%20don't%20have%20assigned%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAwareness%20of%20those%20concerns%2C%20and%20the%20need%20to%20provide%20different%20types%20of%20workspaces%20to%20accommodate%20a%20range%20of%20workers%2C%20is%20growing%2C%20Neil%20Murray%2C%20global%20CEO%20of%20real%20estate%20management%20services%20at%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%20firm%20JLL%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20clients%20are%20figuring%20neurodiversity%20into%20their%20planning%2C%20into%20their%20occupancy%20planning%2C%20into%20their%20layouts%20like%20never%20before%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20something%20Travis%20Hollman%20has%20seen%20in%20conversations%20with%20Fortune%20500%20companies%2C%20universities%2C%20and%20workplace%20design%20firms%2C%20he%20said.%20In%202024%2C%20his%20Dallas-area%20company%2C%20MeSpace%2C%20began%20marketing%20booths%20for%20people%20who%20want%20an%20escape%20from%20open-plan%20spaces%20without%20being%20in%20a%20soundproof%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHollman%2C%20whose%20childhood%20struggles%20with%20attention%20deficit%20disorder%20and%20dyslexia%20included%20failing%20third%20grade%20because%20of%20difficulty%20reading%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20doing%20more%20to%20support%20neurodivergent%20workers%20could%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bgame%20changer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHollman%20said%20that%20without%20the%20right%20accommodations%2C%20some%20neurodivergent%20workers%20might%20quit%20or%20be%20fired%2C%20for%20example%2C%20because%20they%20can't%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20put%20them%20in%20this%20position%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264886d62-4a16-4fcf-806a-9d6b773f1ca8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuilding%20skills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20BofA's%20Support%20Services%20group%2C%20where%20Price%20works%2C%20many%20of%20the%20tasks%20the%20workers%20take%20on%20are%20ones%20the%20company%20once%20sent%20to%20vendors%2C%20Mark%20Feinour%2C%20the%20unit's%20executive%20director%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20do%20it%20more%20efficiently%20and%20more%20accurately%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Feinour%20oversees%20teams%20in%20Boston%2C%20Dallas%2C%20and%20Belfast%2C%20Maine%2C%20that%20handle%20some%2027%20million%20items%20annually%20for%20the%20bank's%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Price%2C%20who%20has%20a%20degree%20in%20math%20and%20who's%20always%20wanted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-says-job-applications-stood-out-when-hiring-research-work-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20in%20