he%20message%20is%20clear%3A%20If%20you're%20in%20a%20profession%20that%20requires%20you%20to%20think%20for%20a%20living%2C%20you%20better%20think%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20long%20channeled%20anti-elite%20sentiment%20for%20his%20political%20benefit%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20MAGA%20message%20that%20helped%20propel%20him%20to%20the%20White%20House.%20He%20knows%20that%20for%20many%20Americans%2C%20highfalutin%20lawyers%20and%20university%20professors%20aren't%20exactly%20popular%20figures.%20And%20he%20knows%20that%20attacking%20knowledge%20workers%20won't%20cost%20him%20or%20his%20party%20much%20support%2C%20since%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20vote%20for%20Republicans%20than%20Americans%20without%20a%20college%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20dominant%20political%20cleavage%20right%20now%20in%20this%20country%20is%20if%20you%20have%20a%20college%20education%2C%20you're%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20vote%20for%20Donald%20Trump%20or%20vote%20Republican%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Daniel%20Drezner%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20at%20Tufts%20University.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20was%20drawing%20up%20a%20master%20plan%20of%20how%20I%20would%20weaken%20the%20groups%20that%20are%20opposed%20to%20me%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20look%20that%20different%20from%20what%20he's%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrust%20in%20the%20professions%20Trump%20is%20targeting%20is%20in%20steep%20decline.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F655106%2Famericans-ratings-professions-stay-historically-low.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%3C%2Fa%3E%20poll%20of%20Americans%20found%20respondents%20had%20net%20negative%20views%20of%20lawyers%2C%20reporters%2C%20bankers%2C%20and%20business%20executives.%20In%20terms%20of%20public%20opinion%2C%20TV%20reporters%20ranked%20below%20car%20salespeople.%20And%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20institutional%20trust%2C%20another%20Gallup%20poll%20found%20newspapers%2C%20big%20business%2C%20and%20television%20news%20were%20among%20those%20with%20the%20least.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20public%20imagination%2C%20the%20jobs%20Trump%20is%20going%20after%20aren't%20ones%20typically%20thought%20of%20as%20authentically%20American%20in%20the%20way%2C%20say%2C%20an%20autoworker%20or%20a%20coal%20miner%20is.%20Unless%20they're%20directly%20affected%20by%20Trump's%20actions%2C%20many%20Americans%20aren't%20losing%20sleep%20at%20night%20wondering%20what%20will%20happen%20to%20some%20nondescript%20professor%20in%20a%20suit%20they%20saw%20on%20CNN.%20A%20recent%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DC1UgGbiUTTo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Daily%20Show%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20tapped%20into%20the%20sentiment.%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20I%20don't%20usually%20root%20for%20Harvard%2C%20because%20they're%20Harvard.%20They've%20got%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20host%20Ronny%20Chieng%20joked.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20rooting%20for%20Jeff%20Bezos%20to%20win%20the%20lottery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20base%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20feels%20slighted%20by%20institutions.%20Katherine%20Cramer%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Wisconsin-Madison%20political%20science%20professor%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc01b1257c2f63775115c1374aad06ba6df235b0b463f3cc95e75679c399099ef%26postID%3D681215a718fa5330632a8ff7%26postSlug%3Dtrumps-knowledge-workers-war-fired-doge-columbia-harvard-big-law-2025-5%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FPolitics-Resentment-Consciousness-Wisconsin-American%252Fdp%252F022634911X%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Politics%20of%20Resentment%3A%20Rural%20Consciousness%20in%20Wisconsin%20and%20the%20Rise%20of%20Scott%20Walker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20sums%20up%20the%20prevailing%20attitude%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20this%20sense%20that%2C%20'Hey%2C%20wait%20a%20minute%2C%20things%20aren't%20working%20out%20for%20me%20the%20way%20they%20should%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20like%20the%20way%20everything%20is%20set%20up%20is%20not%20set%20up%20for%20people%20like%20me.'%26quot%3B%20By%20taking%20aim%20at%20those%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Belites%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20is%20able%20to%20create%20a%20clear%20target%20for%20voters%20angry%20about%20what%20they%20view%20as%20a%20rigged%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20hardly%20the%20first%20political%20figure%20to%20decipher%20this%20code.%20As%20the%20historian%20Julian%20Zelizer%20pointed%20out%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2025%2F03%2F03%2Ftrump-george-w-bush-anti-intellectualism-expertise-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20column%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Foreign%20Policy%2C%20you%20can%20trace%20the%20anti-intellectual%20political%20appeal%20back%20to%20Richard%20Nixon%20calling%20his%20vice%20presidential%20opponent%20an%20%26quot%3Begghead%26quot%3B%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20George%20W.%20Bush's%20regular-guy%20schtick%20in%20the%202000s.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20very%20adept%20at%20stepping%20in%20and%20deflecting%20the%20anger%2C%20the%20class%20anger%2C%20so%20that%20it%20wasn't%20expressed%20against%20economic%20elites%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Williams%2C%20the%20law%20professor.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20expressed%20against%20cultural%20elites%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20these%20college%20grads%20in%20government%20jobs%2C%20lawyers%2C%20doctors%2C%20science.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20emphasis%20on%20masculinity%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20doesn't%20just%20manifest%20in%20his%20rhetoric%20about%20bringing%20back%20manufacturing%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-leaving-doge-firings-rifs-trump-federal-workforce-cuts-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20and%20Musk%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehave%20channeled%20it%20into%20the%20way%20they're%20firing%20federal%20workers.%20Part%20of%20the%20way%20the%20president%20rose%20to%20fame%20was%20by%20telling%20people%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20fired%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20national%20TV.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-tesla-layoffs-hhs-terminations-doge-federal-workers-trump-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk's%20business%20playbook%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20similarly%20involved%20swooping%20in%20on%20companies%20and%20axing%20thousands%20of%20employees.%20Now%20they're%20bringing%20that%20same%20%26quot%3Boff-with-their-heads%26quot%3B%20style%20to%20Americans%20who%20work%20with%20their%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20honest%2C%20knowledge%20workers%20share%20some%20of%20the%20blame%20for%20their%20own%20unpopularity.%20Intellectual%20elites%20can%20be%20smug%20and%20condescending.%20Some%20of%20them%20look%20down%20on%20Trump%20and%20his%20voters%2C%20or%20at%20least%20make%20them%20feel%20like%20they%20do.%20College-educated%20people%20are%20also%20a%20minority%20%E2%80%94%20about%2038%25%20of%20Americans%20have%20a%20college%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20who%20have%20outsize%20power%20in%20our%20society.%20%26quot%3BWe%20tend%20to%20be%20the%20ones%20in%20professions%2C%26quot%3B%20Cramer%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20the%20ones%20making%20decisions%2C%20and%20there's%20lots%20of%20people%20feeling%20like%20whoever%20is%20making%20the%20decisions%20does%20not%20understand%20my%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20professions%20Trump%20is%20targeting%20are%20important%20ones.%20Nobody%20likes%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20until%20they%20need%20one.%20(Sorry%2C%20lawyers.)%20Universities%20are%20a%20critical%20and%20cost-effective%20engine%20of%20economic%20growth%20and%20technological%20innovation.%20Federal%20workers%20deliver%20essential%20aid%20and%20services%20to%20millions%20of%20Americans%20every%20day.%20Journalists%20help%20hold%20the%20powerful%20to%20account.%20The%20more%20we%20undermine%20these%20professions%20and%20deter%20people%20from%20entering%20them%20altogether%2C%20the%20more%20everyone%20will%20suffer.%20A%20thriving%20economy%20needs%20workers%20of%20all%20kinds%2C%20even%20the%20fancy%20ones%20in%20nice%20offices%20who%20may%20not%20know%20how%20to%20change%20a%20tire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20now%2C%20America's%20knowledge%20workers%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20pickle.%20The%20president%20has%20figured%20out%20they're%20an%20effective%20foil.%20And%20thanks%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-recession-hiring-slump-jobs-tech-industry-applications-rejection-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite-collar%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20things%20aren't%20great%20for%20them%20economically%2C%20either.%20In%20Trump's%20calculus%2C%20professional%20elites%20have%20become%20boogeymen%20on%20par%20with%20immigrants%20in%20the%20country%20illegally%20and%20wind%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20unclear%20is%20whether%20the%20attack%20on%20intellectual%20elites%20is%20an%20actual%20vote%20getter%2C%20or%20whether%20it's%20just%20reinforcing%20preexisting%20divides.%20Jason%20Husser%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Elon%20University%20Poll%2C%20says%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20moves%20like%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20penalizing%20law%20firms%20will%20cause%20swing%20voters%20to%20abandon%20Republicans%20in%202026%20or%202028.%20It%20depends%2C%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20on%20how%20the%20battle%20against%20knowledge%20workers%20is%20framed.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it's%20conveyed%20as%20a%20story%20where%20Trump%20is%20the%20protagonist%20and%20the%20intelligentsia%20is%20the%20antagonist%2C%26quot%3B%20Husser%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20he's%20better%20able%20to%20capture%20his%20party%20and%20move%20a%20few%20independents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Americans%20come%20to%20realize%20how%20much%20their%20lives%20depend%20on%20the%20work%20of%20white-collar%20professionals%2C%20Trump's%20attacks%20on%20college-educated%20elites%20could%20wind%20up%20costing