0future%20%E2%80%94%20has%20thrown%20my%20generation%20into%20a%20state%20I've%20come%20to%20think%20of%20as%20Millennial%20Retirement%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nirsonline.org%2Freports%2Fgenerations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPanic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20I'm%20counting%20on%20my%20401(k)%20to%20fund%20my%20golden%20years%2C%20how%20do%20I%20retire%20during%20an%20apocalypse%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20it%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-lower-home-prices-property-values-places-hit-hardest-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20little%20we're%20factoring%20its%20long-term%20effects%20into%20our%20economic%20planning%20%E2%80%94%20that%20first%20triggered%20my%20retirement%20panic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202018%2C%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20projected%202040%20%E2%80%94%20the%20year%20I%20turn%2060%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20moment%20the%20world%20will%20likely%20warm%20by%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20threshold%20at%20which%20the%20effects%20of%20global%20warming%20will%20become%20irreversibly%20catastrophic.%20The%20following%20summer%2C%20I%20caught%20a%20panel%20during%20London's%20Climate%20Week%20that%20shook%20me%20even%20more.%20Economists%20who%20advise%20major%20insurance%20companies%20and%20pension%20funds%20presented%20findings%20from%20a%20model%20about%20what%20climate%20change%20will%20do%20to%20the%20world%20economy.%20At%20the%20highest%20projected%20temperatures%2C%20they%20estimated%2C%20GDPs%20would%20plummet%20by%2030%25%20by%202080%20in%20every%20country%20they%20modeled%2C%20including%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20panel%2C%20I%20asked%20one%20of%20the%20presenters%2C%20Willemijn%20Verdegaal%2C%20what%20I%20should%20do%20to%20prepare%20for%20retirement%2C%20assuming%20the%20Earth%20stays%20on%20its%20current%20warming%20trajectory.%20%26quot%3BIn%20all%20honesty%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20very%20little%20point%20in%20you%20saving%20anything%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20echoed%20that%20pessimism.%20G%C3%BCnther%20Thallinger%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Allianz%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20insurance%20companies%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Fclimate-risk-insurance-future-capitalism-g%25C3%25BCnther-thallinger-smw5f%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20without%20urgent%20action%20to%20curtail%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20insurance%20industry%20could%20collapse.%20If%20homes%20aren't%20insured%2C%20banks%20would%20stop%20issuing%20mortgages%2C%20and%20markets%20would%20go%20into%20free%20fall.%20%26quot%3BCapitalism%20as%20we%20know%20it%20ceases%20to%20be%20viable%2C%26quot%3B%20Thallinger%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20scared%20the%20hell%20out%20of%20me.%20What's%20the%20point%20in%20planning%20for%20a%20retirement%20that%20may%20never%20happen%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20no%20economic%20model%20can%20fully%20account%20for%20all%20the%20unknowns%20about%20climate%20accurately%20enough%20to%20put%20a%20firm%20number%20on%20its%20financial%20impact.%20And%20if%20the%20world%20invests%20dramatically%20in%20reducing%20emissions%2C%20the%20economy%20could%20escape%20some%20of%20the%20most%20dire%20forecasts.%20But%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20believe%20in%20any%20single%20prediction%20to%20conclude%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-lower-home-prices-property-values-places-hit-hardest-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20make%20retirement%20look%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eway%20different%20for%20millennials%20than%20it%20has%20for%20boomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20number%20is%20false%20precision%2C%20false%20accuracy%2C%20or%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20Gernot%20Wagner%2C%20a%20climate%20economist%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20know%20is%2C%20it%20is%20less%20certain%20that%20I'm%20going%20to%20have%20a%20stable%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20millennials%20started%20off%20our%20adulthoods%20at%20a%20retirement%20disadvantage.%20While%20my%20parents%20and%20their%20friends%20benefited%20from%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20periods%20of%20economic%20growth%20in%20American%20history%2C%20my%20generation%20has%20experienced%20one%20upheaval%20after%20another.%20I%20graduated%20from%20college%20right%20into%20the%20dot-com%20bust.%20The%20Great%20Recession%20of%202008%20came%20just%20as%20I%20finished%20graduate%20school.%20We're%20the%20best-educated%20generation%2C%20but%20that%20distinction%20means%20that%20many%20millennials%20are%20saddled%20with%20crushing%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrr.bc.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2FIB_21_3-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20Research%20at%20Boston%20College%20found%20that%20millennials%20were%20%26quot%3Bwell%20behind%26quot%3B%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20baby%20boomers%20at%20the%20same%20point%20in%20their%20working%20lives.%20Millennials%20in%20their%20late%2030s%20were%20three%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20paying%20off%20student%20loans%20than%20boomers%20were%20at%20the%20same%20age%2C%20and%20twice%20more%20likely%20than%20Gen%20Xers.%20All%20told%2C%20millennials%20had%20accumulated%20about%2015%25%20less%20wealth%20than%20boomers%20%E2%80%94%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E36%25%20less%20than%20Gen%20Xers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20got%20a%20break%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20thanks%20partly%20to%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20pause%20on%20student%20loan%20payments.%20By%202022%2C%20the%20Center%20for%20Retirement%20Research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrr.bc.edu%2Fis-the-retirement-picture-for-millennials-looking-better%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20millennials%20had%20not%20only%20caught%20up%20to%20the%20wealth%20trajectories%20of%20previous%20generations%20but%20had%20actually%20surpassed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20reprieve%20was%20short-lived.%20Since%20taking%20office%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20rescinded%20the%20Biden-era%20break%20on%20student%20loans.%20And%20the%20market%20plunge%20in%20early%20April%20brought%20back%20memories%20of%20the%20economic%20shocks%20we've%20experienced%20at%20earlier%20stages%20of%20our%20careers.%20%26quot%3BAnother%20major%20downturn%20could%20vanish%20whatever%20progress%20we%20have%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20Nilufer%20Gok%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20Boston%20College%20report%2C%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20recent%20events%20have%20called%20into%20question%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-is-doing-retirement-all-wrong-boomers-aging-longevity-happiness-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20assumptions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20ways%20that%20are%20even%20more%20alarming.%20Economists%20warn%20that%20Trump's%20tariffs%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20permanent%20realignment%20of%20the%20world%20economy%2C%20making%20daily%20life%20far%20more%20expensive.%20I%20worry%20that%20both%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20could%20see%20our%20wages%20fall%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20devalues%20the%20kind%20of%20work%20we%20do.%20And%20Social%20Security%2C%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20America's%20retirement%20system%2C%20is%20projected%20to%20face%20a%20shortfall%20that%20will%20force%20benefit%20cuts%20unless%20Congress%20takes%20action%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2026%2F02%2F20240211_CHP_Primus_FixingSS_Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2033%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Millennials%2C%20having%20already%20lived%20through%20a%20staggering%20period%20of%20technological%20and%20economic%20change%2C%20now%20face%20the%20prospect%20of%20even%20greater%20upheaval%20in%20the%20decades%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20my%20Millennial%20Retirement%20Panic%20mounted%2C%20I%20asked%20my%20financial%20advisor%20%E2%80%94%20then%20in%20his%2070s%20%E2%80%94%20what%20I%20could%20do%20to%20better%20prepare%20for%20an%20ominous%20future.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%20to%20live%20your%20life%20like%20there'll%20be%20a%20disaster%20at%20the%20end%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20financial%20planners%20and%20climate%20forecasters%20offered%20me%20the%20same%20advice.%20There's%20not%20a%20whole%20lot%20that%20any%20of%20us%20can%20do%20as%20individuals%20to%20protect%20our%20finances%20from%20the%20kind%20of%20massive%2C%20macroeconomic%20shifts%20we're%20facing.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20certainly%20create%20a%20hedge%20against%20risks%20within%20the%20portfolio%20composition%2C%20but%20that%20only%20goes%20so%20far%2C%26quot%3B%20Jesse%20Keenan%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20climate%20change%20researcher%20and%20professor%20at%20Tulane%20University%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20difficult%2C%20I%20think%2C%20to%20do%20it%20at%20an%20individual%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20they're%20right%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20take%20some%20sort%20of%20action%2C%20to%20increase%20my%20chances%20of%20enjoying%20a%20secure%20and%20comfortable%20retirement%20in%20the%20face%20of%20looming%20disaster.%20When%20COVID-19%20shut%20down%20New%20York%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Michigan%2C%20a%20state%20we%20chose%20because%20scientists%20predict%20it%20would%20emerge%20relatively%20unscathed%20by%20warming%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20not%20long%20after%20we%20arrived%2C%20the%20neighborhood%20we%20selected%20as%20a%20safe%20haven%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretiree-bought-hurricane-proof-florida-house-in-hurricane-milton-path-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20weather%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20flooded%20by%20unusually%20heavy%20rains%20and%20was%20ultimately%20declared%20a%20federal%20disaster%20area.%20There%20wasn't%20much%20of%20a%20job%20market%20for%20me%20in%20Michigan%2C%20which%20sapped%20my%20earnings%20and%20made%20saving%20harder.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20also%20didn't%20have%20a%20social%20network%20that%20could%20help%20me%20find%20a%20better%20job.%20We%20eventually%20returned%20to%20New%20York%2C%20feeling%20as%20helpless%20about%20old%20age%20as%20we%20did%20when%20we%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20where%20does%20that%20leave%20us%3F%20For%20now%2C%20we're%20staying%20on%20our%20retirement%20savings%20track%20as%20best%20we%20can%2C%20mainly%20because%20we%20don't%20know%20what%20else%20to%20do.%20Regardless%20of%20what%20the%20future%20brings%2C%20we%20know%20that%20any%20savings%20are%20better%20than%20none.%20But%20the%20more%20I%20think%20about%20retirement%2C%20the%20more%20convinced%20I%20am%20that%20our%20current%20assumptions%20about%20it%20are%20just%20plain%20wrong.%20The%20ways%20our%20parents%20built%20wealth%20for%20retirement%20may%20not%20work%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20lies%20ahead%2C%20I%20know%20it%20won't%20help%20to%20panic.%20But%20we%20also%20need%20to%20be%20clear-eyed%20about%20the%20external%20risks%20to%20our%20individual%20retirement%20plans.%20Our%20investments%20and%20our%20homes%20and%20our%20jobs%20don't%20exist%20in%20a%20bubble%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20projections%20we%20make%20about%20them%20need%20to%20take%20into%20account%20all%20the%20external%20factors%20that%20threaten%20to%20disrupt%20them%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20new%20and%20unprecedented%20ways.%20It's%20necessary%20to%20make%20assumptions%20about%20our%20retirement.%20But%20our%20old%20ones%20don't%20feel%20up%20to%20what's%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJ.%20Lester%20Feder%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20based%20in%20Brooklyn.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-millennial-retirement-panic-boomer-parents-saving-401k-market-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746346742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681503baa466d2b74ab4e3f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-millennial-retirement-panic-boomer-parents-saving-401k-market-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20millennial%2C%20my%20dream%20is%20to%20eventually%20retire%20like%20my%20boomer%20parents.%20I'm%20skeptical%20I%20ever%20will.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(J.%20Lester%20Feder)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A90%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-millennial-retirement-panic-boomer-parents-saving-401k-market-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jaguar%20Land%20Rover%20resumes%20car%20exports%20to%20US%20post%20Trump%20tariff%20pause%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746346356000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fjaguar-land-rover-resumes-car-exports-to-us-post-trump-tariff-pause-report-125050300614_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20shipments%20of%20JLR%20vehicles%20bound%20for%20the%20US%20for%20almost%20a%20month%20left%20Britain%20on%20Wednesday%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Three%20Army%20soldiers%20killed%20after%20truck%20falls%20into%20deep%20gorge%20in%20J%26amp%3BK's%20Ramban%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746346338000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22