to%20Rs%20266%20per%20day%2C%20falling%20well%20below%20the%20national%20minimum%20wage%20threshold%20of%20Rs%20178.%20Their%20income%20accounts%20for%20only%2024%20percent%20of%20household%20expenses%2C%20highlighting%20the%20entrenched%20gender%20and%20economic%20disparities.%20Lack%20of%20formal%20recognition%20not%20only%20undermines%20their%20earnings%20but%20also%20cuts%20them%20off%20from%20basic%20social%20security%20protections%20and%20dignified%20work%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolicy%20gaps%20have%20further%20exacerbated%20their%20vulnerability.%20The%20repeal%20of%20the%20Beedi%20Workers%20Welfare%20Fund%20Act%2C%201976%2C%20in%202019%20led%20to%20the%20discontinuation%20of%20key%20welfare%20measures%20such%20as%20scholarships%20for%20workers%E2%80%99%20children%20and%20access%20to%20free%20healthcare%20despite%20the%20well-documented%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20%3Cem%3Ebeedi%3C%2Fem%3E%20work%2C%20including%20skin%20ailments%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20basic%20infrastructure%20like%20toilets.%20This%20has%20left%20many%20workers%20without%20state%20benefits%20that%20once%20served%20as%20a%20crucial%20safety%20net.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mssnmp.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMahila%20Shram%20Sewa%20Nyas%20(MSSN)%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20has%20stepped%20in%20with%20a%20community-driven%20model%20rooted%20in%20policy%20advocacy%20and%20empowerment.%20Working%20across%20seven%20districts%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20MSSN%20supports%20women%20informal%20workers%20through%20livelihood%20trainings%2C%20cooperative%20credit%20societies%2C%20leadership%20development%2C%20and%20legal%20aid.%20They%20also%20work%20with%20local%20governments%20to%20restore%20and%20strengthen%20welfare%20provisions%2C%20ensuring%20that%20women%20workers%E2%80%99%20voices%20are%20represented%20in%20policy%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommun